Articles.Content: Any good probe parts mods? I've got the novapunch and b9 probes, and I don't like AIES. Any others?
FASA has one, as does Interstellar. but they arent very probe heavy.
What kind of things are you looking for exactly?
Lack's SXT mod has some great probe parts http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/24906-WIP-LLL-Lack-Luster-Labs-LLL-0-10-7-3b-25FEB2014-SXT-0-9-15MAR2014

What kind of things are you looking for exactly?

Looking for probe bodies, engines comms gear etc.

Taki117, all of the ones in interstellar are high end devices like plasma thrusters that you can't really use early in career mode, though I do have the mod installed.
AIES has a lot of probe stuff in it. It adds - don't know - 5 or 6 probe command modules and of course other modules to complete that. It's worth a look.

They said they didn't like AIES
RLA Stockalike has lots of great probe-sized engines, fuel tanks, RCS and some structural parts. No gear or one-piece bodies, though. And I'm not sure if it's integrated into career.
